1. Request the Municipal Engineer to replace the unserviceable transformer and ensure that the potable water system is operational. Moreover, monitor and ensure that all PPAs implemented are functioning optimally to achieve maximum benefits from its intended purpose;
2. Monitor and implement timely the PPAs so that the beneficiaries can enjoy the benefits due to them; and
3. Request the Municipal Accountant, in coordination with the Heads of implementing units, to implement proper liquidation of the amount granted as well as the refund of excess project funds to the Source Agency or transfer to its General Fund, if allowed in the terms of grant.

1. Conduct comprehensive analysis of funding sources and ensure that PPAs are properly linked with those sources and service delivery outcomes; prioritize projects which are ready for implementation for constituents to enjoy the benefits at the earliest opportunity;
2. Maximize the implementation of PPAs under the 20% LDF that are envisioned to help in the attainment of social, economic and environmental development;
3. Observed the regulations under the procurement regulations under the Procurement Law and require the prospective bidders to expedite filing their eligibility requirements in order that they can participate in the bidding process of the LGU.

1. Enforce the policy on waste segregation as mandated under RA 9003;
2. Prepare a revised 10-year Integrated Solid Waste Management Plan and submit to the National Solid Waste Management Commission for approval;
3. Use a sanitary landfill for the final depository of waste.

The Municipal Treasurer in coordination with other concerned Agency Officials should initiate immediate necessary measures for the eventual writing-off of the account in accordance with existing rules and regulations on the dropping of accounts. All remaining remedies, if any, for the recovery of the said account should be exhausted;
The write-off of the account should only be made upon the approval of the Commission on Audit.  After the write-off of the account, an appropriate account be established (i.e. Accounts Receivable) to maintain a receivable account against the depository bank or to any accountable persons that may be determined; and
The Municipal Treasurer should strictly adhere to follow guidelines on placement of excess/unused fund in Time Deposit as may be required under existing municipal ordinances and that the financial statement of the authorized depository banks should be evaluated first before investing time deposits with their banks.
